&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We’re on a mission to empower animal healthcare professionals with opportunities to earn more and achieve greater flexibility in their careers and personal lives.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Powered by groundbreaking technology, Roo has built the industry-leading veterinary staffing platform, connecting Veterinarians, Technicians, and Assistants with animal hospitals for relief work and hiring opportunities. Roo empowers the largest network of over 20,000 veterinary professionals to help more than 9,000 animal hospitals provide quality care to more pets.&lt;br&gt;Together, we’ve provided more than&amp;nbsp; 3 million hours of healthcare, helping Veterinarians earn more than $200 million.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;About the Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re in the builder era. Prompt-to-feature workflows are real, AI coding tools are the new norm, and the teams that win will be the ones who set up the right infrastructure to move fast with them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re hiring an engineer to own the frontend platform at Roo. That includes our design system, shared UI architecture, developer tooling, AI-assisted workflows, and the technical foundation that helps every team member build polished, consistent product experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;re creating the workflows that unlock capacity for the whole team. You&#39;ll identify and build the highest-leverage improvements to our frontend platform, from design system tooling and AI integrations to shared infrastructure, developer experience, and platform modernization. Your customers are every builder at Roo—engineers, designers, and AI agents. Success in this role means making it dramatically easier for all of them to build great product experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a high-agency, find-it-fix-it-ship-it role. You&#39;ll identify the problems, scope the solutions, and build them, without needing a full squad behind you. The right person is already using AI tools to move faster than anyone around them and sees this as a chance to do that at platform scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
