&lt;li&gt;Own the long-term technical direction of Roo&#39;s frontend platform, including the systems, tooling, and architecture that power development across web and mobile.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product and Design to evolve our design system as a foundational platform rather than a standalone library.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make our design system effortless to consume by engineers, designers, and AI agents through thoughtful integrations, documentation, tooling, and developer workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead platform initiatives like framework upgrades, React Native modernization, Expo adoption, and shared library evolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the migration of legacy components to our v2 design system — including the tooling and documentation that let the rest of the team complete the migration themselves.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish patterns that let engineers ship new pages and flows quickly from a component library that&#39;s built for how people actually build in 2026.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve developer experience through shared tooling, automation, documentation, templates, and workflows that increase engineering velocity.&lt;/li&gt;
